  "texts": [
    "As such, attention allocation is subject not just to descriptive analysis but to normative assessment as well.",
    "There are, for instance, better and worse ways of allocating our attention in the service of both knowledge acquisition and practical ends.",
    "Thus, there are both epistemic and prudential norms of attention.",
    "Checking your calendar is a good way to verify the location of your meeting; and you should watch for traffic as you walk there, assuming you want to arrive in one piece.",
    "Moreover, if you've promised to be there, your attention allocation is also subject to moral norms."
  ],
